The paper discusses model selection and classification tasks, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Bayesian networks and Naive Bayes classifiers also suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and data mining. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Data Mining) are the most likely sub-categories. The mention of mixtures and augmenting Naive Bayes also suggests a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
